survey_response.review_text:
My 3month old baby developed a cough which inspite of showing 3 different doctors was just not reducing , each time dose of medication and nebulisation was only being increased without any improvement in the baby. It was 2months into the cough and Finally after a friends recommendation visited dr Jagadish Chinnappa who examined the baby and advised to stop all nebulisation , explained the cause for cough and follow certain simple steps and medicines. Within 10 days time we could finally see improvement in the cough and we are very happy to say in a months time the cough stopped as well. 
Shall forever be grateful to dr Jagadish Chinappa.
Definitely recommend Dr. Jagadish Chinnappa with the vast experience he has.  He gets to the core of the issue and gives best advice

We went to take a second opinion while our regular doctor was not around, and he told us our regular doctor is his student. Also he commented on my communication skills instead of just asking me to be more clear. He dismissed our concerns, didn't give the reports more than a passing glance. He is an experienced doctor, but he can do without making unnecessary comments.

We have recently relocated to Bangalore and were struggling to find a good paediatrician . Doctor Jagadish epitomizes the phrase  "experience speaks volumes" . The care and control doctor displayed really gave us the confidence that we have finally got a good doctor for our lil munchkin.  
Kindly note this is not casting aspersions  on other doctors ability ; it's just that we found what we were looking out for.

He is one of the great doctor in Bangalore. He is understands the bigger picture of current situation of kid and he comes up with plan. And a great thing about this doctor is, he considers other available options and explains to the parents very clearly.

When my son was 7-8 months, he was getting frequent cold and cough. I visited my regular paediatrician 5 times in that month, antibiotics were changed every time and my son was declared asthmatic. My friend suggested me to consult Dr. Jagadish Chinnappa and Dr. asked us to make some life style changes. Its been more than a year now and my son is fine. Can't thank him enough.

The doctor is very very rude. His staff are even worse than the doctor. They are not helpful, extremely rude and unprofessional and talk to you with no respect and act like they are doing you favor. He charges Rs.1000 for consultation. ** ******** ** ******* *** ******* **** **** ** ***** ******* ** *** **** ** ** ******** ** *** ****** *** ****** ** ***** ** ***** **** *** ****** ***** *** ** *** ******* **** ********** ** ** ************* ***********

Since our baby was born in Manipal, we visit this hospital once in a while for distinctive medical assistance. With Dr. Jagadish Chinnappa, it was an excellent session. His advice and cooperation have fulfilled all our medical requirements. We are happy with the experience.

He is the one who gets to the root of problem and his eyes depicts ‘experience’. Since last 4 years he is our paediatrician for our daughter and now we are completely trusting him for our 2nd new born as well. *** **** **** ************* ** **** * *** ****

**** **** ********Never prescribes unnecessary medicines or tests. 
Our son was suffering from severe ear infection, and was given heavy antibiotics.. but after completion of course still fever was coming..that time Dr.Jagdish took the call to stop medicine and to our surprise despite of the fluid in ear and no medicine our child started improving just with anti allergymedicine after 2 months of illness. He understood our worries and explained everything very nicely.

Doctor's even don't care whether patient is a poor person or a rich person. what is his financial background. they cut all persons pocket in the same way without any mercy.
